': 42, 'rejected_prediction_tokens': None, 'text_tokens': 84}, 'prompt_tokens_details': {'audio_tokens': None, 'cached_tokens': None, 'text_tokens': 4762}}, 'model_provider': 'openai', 'model_name': 'qwen3.5-plus', 'system_fingerprint': None, 'id': 'chatcmpl-0f1af2e2-45ad-92df-b88d-cf5d698cf9dd', 'finish_reason': 'tool_calls', 'logprobs': None}, name='researcher', id='lc_run--019c9dd5-4c7b-7fe3-8ea4-00b4cafde448-0', tool_calls=[{'name': 'common_search', 'args': {'query': 'three marine species named after person died January 2022'}, 'id': 'call_06f9b1dee07d4ea689632d0f', 'type': 'tool_call'}], invalid_tool_calls=[], usage_metadata={'input_tokens': 4762, 'output_tokens': 84, 'total_tokens': 4846, 'input_token_details': {}, 'output_token_details': {'reasoning': 42}}), ToolMessage(content=[{'type': 'text', 'text': '# 搜索结果\n标题：权威例句\nURL：http://dict.youdao.com/example/auth/a_bian/\n站点名称：有道网\n发布时间：\n摘要：\nBidean Nam  Bian  is  a  Munro -  a  mountain higher than 3, 000ft - with  a  number of different climbs. \nBBC:  Glencoe avalanche: Three victims named\nIn January, four people died in Glencoe after they were caught up in  a  snow slide on Bidean Nam  Bian . \nBBC:  Daily avalanche reports for Scottish mountains wound up\n\n---\n\n标题：2025年度海洋摄影师大赛-海洋保护。影响力奖：第1名：雨果·布雷特，法罗群岛一头长肢领航鲸的胎儿毫无生气地躺在其母亲的尸体下方。第2名...\nURL：https://m.toutiao.com/a1850620858833992/\n站点名称：今日头条\n发布时间：\n摘要：\n2025年度海洋摄影师大赛-海洋保护。影响力奖：第1名：雨果·布雷特，法罗群岛一头长肢领航鲸的胎儿毫无生气地躺在其母亲的尸体下方。第2名：丹尼尔·弗洛曼，印度尼西亚三条鲨鱼死在凤尾鱼的网中。第3名：克劳迪奥·莫雷诺·马德里，澳大利亚这头座头鲸，它被渔网死死缠住，还遭到了几十条鲨鱼的追逐。第4名：安德鲁·沙利文-哈斯金斯，夏威夷一位来自帕帕哈瑙莫夸基亚海洋垃圾项目（PMDP）的受过专门训练的技术人员，一边小心翼翼地穿梭在数千只信天翁雏鸟之间，一边拖着一张巨大的幽灵网。第5名：杰西·米勒，美国华盛顿州得梅因的雷东多海滩发现了六鳃鲨。第6名：吉安卡洛·马扎雷塞，菲律宾在夜晚的黑暗中，一只小纸鹦鹉螺紧贴着塑料瓶盖。第7名：亨利·斯皮尔斯，墨西哥这只绿海龟是被船撞死的，对于一个濒临灭绝的物种来说，这是一次不自然和不必要的死亡。第8名：朱莉娅·奥克斯，西班牙这张照片捕捉到了地中海一艘小型底拖网渔船上罕见的时刻。第9名：纳特纳查·查图拉皮塔蒙，孟加拉国在这幅充满活力的海港场景中，渔民们在日出时分从一艘木制渔船上卸下他们的捕获物。第10名：诺姆·科特勒，菲律宾9头鲸鲨靠近船只等待投喂，还有更多的游泳者和潜水者在那里观赏它们。这种情况每天都在发生。第11名：理查德·史密斯，巴布亚新几内亚“25年后，我回到了巴布亚新几内亚的米尔恩湾，回想起那里令人惊叹的珊瑚和生物多样性，”史密斯说。“可悲的是，我们的第一次潜水就看到了我所见过的最严重的珊瑚白化现象。第12名：尤安·克尔达维德，南极洲过去20年里，磷虾捕捞量增长了三倍。#摄影 #摄影作品欣赏 #海洋保护\n\n---\n\n标题：红海与印尼海域发现五种新海马，命名致敬科研先锋\nURL：https://baijiahao.baidu.com/s?id=1826086105331525678\n站点名称：百家号\n发布时间：\n摘要：\n这一新物种是以著名水下摄影师赫尔穆特-德贝柳斯的名字来命名的。德贝柳斯率领的探险队成功捕获了这些生活在红海区域的微小生物，并经过了长达十年的观察与研究，最终在2009年1月的研究杂志上描述了这一新发现。对于这一荣誉，德贝柳斯表示深感欣慰，尽管他的名字已被其他几种海洋生物所采用，但能在海马家族中增添一员，无疑是一件令人兴奋的事情。\n塞费恩矮海马\n这一新物种的命名源于潜水员迈克·塞费恩。与德贝柳斯矮海马相似，它也是在2008年12月的研究杂志上被正式命名的。来自加拿大麦吉尔大学的萨拉·劳里是该杂志的另一位合著者，她在电子邮件中表示，这些新发现的海马能够被科学家们公认，完全归功于当地的潜水引导员和摄影师们。正是他们分享的精美照片，为科学家们提供了宝贵的研究资料，从而揭示了这些新物种的存在。劳里强调，这是一次真正的团队协作，每个成员都为这一重大发现贡献了自己的力量。\n瓦里岛矮海马\n这一新物种的命名源于其独特的发现地点——印度尼西亚苏拉威西海中央的瓦里岛。近期，在红海和印度尼西亚地区的一系列海洋探索中，科学家们新发现了五种海马，而瓦里岛矮海马便是其中之一，且至今仅在瓦里岛有过发现。\n\n---\n\n标题：List of species named after the COVID-19 pandemic - Wikipedia\nURL：https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_species_named_after_the_COVID-19_pandemic\n站点名称：\n发布时间：\n摘要：\nis suggested in light of these difficult times".\n* Corethrella menini Feijó, Picelli, Ríos-Velásquez & Pessoa, 2021 (Insect, Diptera, Corethrellidae) – "Corethrella menini sp. nov. is named in honor of Dr. Marcelo Menin as a tribute to his important work as a herpetologist, focused on ecology and biology of anurans. Marcelo was a professor of zoology who inspired dozens of zoology students, a beloved friend. He passed away too young during the COVID pandemic." when the speciesʼ name was chosen)".\n* Oxymorus johnprinei Borovec & Meregalli, 2020 (Insect, Coleoptera, Curculionidae) – named "in memory of the late John Prine (1946–2020), American folk singer and songwriter who sadly passed away due to COVID-19 while the authors were completing the paper"', 'id': 'lc_b6eed2bf-001f-455c-a0e2-43782c8520aa'}], name='common_search', id='4dc848e5-7d96-4c96-b0cc-0ce3098a6896', tool_call_id='call_06f9b1dee07d4ea689632d0f'), AIMessage(content='', additional_kwargs={'refusal': None}, response_metadata={'token_usage': {'completion_tokens': 41, 'prompt_tokens': 6122, 'total_tokens': 6163, 'completion_tokens_details': {'accepted_prediction_tokens': None, 'audio_tokens': None, 'reasoning_tokens': 0, 'rejected_prediction_tokens': None, 'text_tokens': 41}, 'prompt_tokens_details': {'audio_tokens': None, 'cached_tokens': None, 'text_tokens': 6122}}, 'model_provider': 'openai', 'model_name': 'qwen3.5-plus', 'system_fingerprint': None, 'id': 'chatcmpl-7b7878dd-af70-9150-9b90-420de836654e', 'finish_reason': 'tool_calls', 'logprobs': None}, name='researcher', id='lc_run--019c9dd5-5ccd-79b1-9c02-2ea543fac5e2-0', tool_calls=[{'name': 'common_search', 'args': {'query': '"died January 8" 2022 museum founder'}, 'id': 'call_382841bf495746e096b5500f', 'type': 'tool_call'}], invalid_tool_calls=[], usage_metadata={'input_tokens': 6122, 'output_tokens': 41, 'total_tokens': 6163, 'input_token_details': {}, 'output_token_details': {'reasoning': 0}}), ToolMessage(content="SYSTEM ALERT: You have used the tool 'common_search' 3 times, which is the limit for a single tool. You MUST switch to a DIFFERENT search tool (e.g., use 'academic_search' or 'web_search' instead of 'common_search'). Using the same tool repeatedly is ineffective. TRY ANOTHER TOOL.", name='common_search', id='4915155d-ef11-495f-9d5b-372650868b52', tool_call_id='call_382841bf495746e096b5500f'), AIMessage(content='', additional_kwargs={'refusal': None}, response_metadata={'token_usage': {'completion_tokens': 270, 'prompt_tokens': 6245, 'total_tokens': 6515, 'completion_tokens_details': {'accepted_prediction_tokens': None, 'audio_tokens': None, 'reasoning_tokens': 227, 'rejected_prediction_tokens': None, 'text_tokens': 270}, 'prompt_tokens_details': {'audio_tokens': None, 'cached_tokens': None, 'text_tokens': 6245}}, 'model_provider': 'openai', 'model_name': 'qwen3.5-plus', 'system_fingerprint': None, 'id': 'chatcmpl-9423dc92-170f-90cc-a251-d87216e7b58f', 'finish_reason': 'tool_calls', 'logprobs': None}, name='researcher', id='lc_run--019c9dd5-618e-7172-baa9-acbfa8218f12-0', tool_calls=[{'name': 'web_search', 'args': {'query': 'died January 8 2022 magazine publisher museum founder'}, 'id': 'call_cb173f2c5a764042973ec49c', 'type': 'tool_call'}], invalid_tool_calls=[], usage_metadata={'input_tokens': 6245, 'output_tokens': 270, 'total_tokens': 6515, 'input_token_details': {}, 'output_token_details': {'reasoning': 227}}), ToolMessage(content='Error: web_search is not a valid tool, try one of [academic_search, wikipedia, common_search, crawl_tool].', name='web_search', id='956cd5a1-1afc-4e08-92be-bc74ed8b189c', tool_call_id='call_cb173f2c5a764042973ec49c', status='error'), AIMessage(content='', additional_kwargs={'refusal': None}, response_metadata={'token_usage': {'completion_tokens': 242, 'prompt_tokens': 6326, 'total_tokens': 6568, 'completion_tokens_details': {'accepted_prediction_tokens': None, 'audio_tokens': None, 'reasoning_tokens': 197, 'rejected_prediction_tokens': None, 'text_tokens': 242}, 'prompt_tokens_details': {'audio_tokens': None, 'cached_tokens': None, 'text_tokens': 6326}}, 'model_provider': 'openai', 'model_name': 'qwen3.5-plus', 'system_fingerprint': None, 'id': 'chatcmpl-c4aac245-5129-917b-bcd7-181ceded23c5', 'finish_reason': 'tool_calls', 'logprobs': None}, name='researcher', id='lc_run--019c9dd5-6fa4-7ea3-aefd-4ada0047a1a4-0', tool_calls=[{'name': 'academic_search', 'args': {'__arg1': 'marine species named after person died January 2022 museum founder'}, 'id': 'call_80fd834c0c844878be45a0f6', 'type': 'tool_call'}], invalid_tool_calls=[], usage_metadata={'input_tokens': 6326, 'output_tokens': 242, 'total_tokens': 6568, 'input_token_details': {}, 'output_token_details': {'reasoning': 197}}), ToolMessage(content='Published: 2022-06-15\nTitle: CMNEROne at SemEval-2022 Task 11: Code-Mixed Named Entity Recognition by leveraging multilingual data\nAuthors: Suman Dowlagar, Radhika Mamidi\nSummary: Identifying named entities is, in general, a practical and challenging task in the field of Natural Language Processing. Named Entity Recognition on the code-mixed text is further challenging due to the linguistic complexity resulting from the nature of the mixing. This paper addresses the submission of team CMNEROne to the SEMEVAL 2022 shared task 11 MultiCoNER. The Code-mixed NER task aimed to identify named entities on the code-mixed dataset. Our work consists of Named Entity Recognition (NER) on the code-mixed dataset by leveraging the multilingual data. We achieved a weighted average F1 score of 0.7044, i.e., 6% greater than the baseline.\n\nPublished: 2022-11-22\nTitle: CHC-COMP 2022: Competition Report\nAuthors: Emanuele De Angelis, Hari Govind V K\nSummary: CHC-COMP 2022 is the fifth edition of the competition of solvers for Constrained Horn Clauses. The competition was run in March 2022; the results were presented at the 9th Workshop on Horn Clauses for Verification and Synthesis held in Munich, Germany, on April 3, 2022. This edition featured six solvers, and eight tracks consisting of sets of linear and nonlinear clauses with constraints over linear integer arithmetic, linear real arithmetic, arrays, and algebraic data types. This report provides an overview of the organization behind the competition runs: it includes the technical details of the competition setup as well as presenting the results of the 2022 edition.\n\nPublished: 2022-06-08\nTitle: Motif Mining and Unsupervised Representation Learning for BirdCLEF 2022\nAuthors: Anthony Miyaguchi, Jiangyue Yu, Bryan Cheungvivatpant, Dakota Dudley, Aniketh Swain\nSummary: We build a classification model for the BirdCLEF 2022 challenge using unsupervised methods. We implement an unsupervised representation of the training dataset using a triplet loss on spectrogram representation of audio motifs. Our best model performs with a score of 0.48 on the public leaderboard.', name='academic_search', id='62ffb4ac-84c3-404c-8314-29772fb80343', tool_call_id='call_80fd834c0c844878be45a0f6'), AIMessage(content='', additional_kwargs={'refusal': None}, response_metadata={'token_usage': {'completion_tokens': 38, 'prompt_t