ll content of at least 1-2 most relevant pages. **Do NOT rely solely on search result snippets**, as they are often incomplete or misleading. Only by crawling the full text can you obtain accurate details for in-depth analysis.\n   - When the task includes time range requirements:\n     - Incorporate appropriate time-based search parameters in your queries (e.g., "after:2020", "before:2023", or specific date ranges)\n     - Ensure search results respect the specified time constraints.\n     - Verify the publication dates of sources to confirm they fall within the required time range.\n   - Use dynamically loaded tools when they are more appropriate for the specific task.\n   - (Recommended) Use the **crawl_tool** to read detailed content from webpages that appear to contain key information in the search results. This allows for deeper reasoning and analysis compared to just using search summaries. Only use URLs from search results or provided by the user.\n5. **Synthesize Information**:\n   - Combine the information gathered from all tools used (search results, crawled content, and dynamically loaded tool outputs).\n   - Ensure the response is clear, concise, and directly addresses the problem.\n   - Track and attribute all information sources with their respective URLs for proper citation.\n   - Include relevant images from the gathered information when helpful.\n\n# Output Format\n\n- Provide a structured response in markdown format.\n- Include the following sections:\n    - **Problem Statement**: Restate the problem for clarity.\n    - **Research Findings**: Organize your findings by topic rather than by tool used. For each major finding:\n        - Perform in-depth analysis, reasoning, and summarization by combining search results with detailed content crawled via **crawl_tool**\n        - Summarize the key information\n        - Track the sources of information but DO NOT include inline citations in the text\n        - Include relevant images if available\n    - **Conclusion**: Provide a synthesized response to the problem based on the gathered information.\n    - **References**: List all sources used with their complete URLs in link reference format at the end of the document. Make sure to include an empty line between each reference for better readability. Use this format for each reference:\n      ```markdown\n      - [Source Title](https://example.com/page1)\n\n      - [Source Title](https://example.com/page2)\n      ```\n- Always output in the locale of **en-US**.\n- DO NOT include inline citations in the text. Instead, track all sources and list them in the References section at the end using link reference format.\n\n# Notes\n\n- **CRITICAL**: NEVER generate URLs on your own. All URLs must come from search tool results. This is a mandatory requirement. **Any fabricated URL will be considered a severe error.**\n- **MANDATORY**: Always start with a web search. Do not rely on your internal knowledge.\n- Always verify the relevance and credibility of the information gathered.\n- If no URL is provided, focus solely on the search results.\n- Never do any math or any file operations.\n- Do not try to interact with the page. The crawl tool can only be used to crawl content.\n- Do not perform any mathematical calculations.\n- Do not attempt any file operations.\n- Proactively invoke `crawl_tool` when search result summaries are insufficient or when detailed data is needed for analysis.\n- Always include source attribution for all information. This is critical for the final report\'s citations.\n- When presenting information from multiple sources, clearly indicate which source each piece of information comes from.\n- Include images using `![Image Description](image_url)` in a separate section.\n- The included images should **only** be from the information gathered **from the search results or the crawled content**. **Never** include images that are not from the search results or the crawled content.\n- Always use the locale of **en-US** for the output.\n- When time range requirements are specified in the task, strictly adhere to these constraints in your search queries and verify that all information provided falls within the specified time period.', additional_kwargs={}, response_metadata={}, id='0177fb99-cbb2-4e0d-b60e-011ad577264e'), HumanMessage(content="# Research Topic\n\nResearch Plan to Identify the Individual\n\n# Completed Research Steps\n\n## Completed Step 1: Search for Individual Matching Death Date and Biographical Details\n\n<finding>\n# Research Report: Identifying the Museum Founder\n\n## Problem Statement\n\nThe research task seeks to identify an individual with the following specific characteristics:\n- Founded a museum established between 1972 and 1975 (inclusive)\n- As of December 31, 2023, the museum is situated on the second floor of a building\n- The museum is located 24 to 25 miles (aerial distance) from a library that opened between 1992 and 1995 and is over 70,000 square feet\n- Was the editor and publisher of a magazine for over thirty years\n- Three marine species have been named in their honor\n- Had a parent with the first name Frank and a sibling with the first name Steve\n- Passed away on January 8 between 2021 and 2023 (inclusive) in a country different from their birthplace\n- Received an award in 2014 in recognition of their work\n\n## Research Findings\n\n### Search Strategy and Limitations\n\nMultiple search queries were executed using the available search tools (common_search and academic_search) to identify the individual matching these highly specific criteria. The searches focused on combinations of:\n- Death date (January 8, 2021-2023)\n- Museum founder status\n- Magazine publisher/editor role\n- Marine species named in honor\n- Family names (Frank as parent, Steve as sibling)\n\n### Key Search Results\n\n**Death Date Searches:**\nSearches for individuals who died on January 8 between 2021-2023 did not return specific matches that could be cross-referenced with the other criteria (museum founder, magazine publisher, marine species honors).\n\n**Marine Species Named After Individuals:**\nSome search results mentioned marine organisms named after various researchers and contributors, including:\n- Several species named after Dr. Otto Maas, Dr. Bernard John McAlice, and others\n- New seahorse species named after underwater photographers and divers (Helmut Debelius, Mike Severn)\n- However, none of these matched the complete profile of the individual in question\n\n**Museum and Magazine Publisher Connections:**\nSearches for museum founders who were also long-time magazine publishers did not yield specific matches with the death date and family name criteria.\n\n### Information Gaps\n\nThe following critical information could not be confirmed through the available searches:\n1. The specific name of the individual matching all criteria\n2. The name and location of the museum founded between 1972-1975\n3. The name of the magazine they edited/published for over 30 years\n4. The three specific marine species named in their honor\n5. Confirmation of parent named Frank and sibling named Steve\n6. The award received in 2014\n7. Birth and death countries to confirm they were different\n8. The library located 24-25 miles from the museum\n\n## Conclusion\n\nBased on the searches conducted, I was unable to definitively identify the individual matching all the specified criteria. The combination of highly specific details (exact death date of January 8, specific year ranges, family member names, number of marine species, and geographic constraints) suggests this is a very specific person, but the available search results did not contain sufficient information to make a positive identification.\n\nThe research was limited by:\n- Maximum search tool call limit (5 calls)\n- Search results that did not contain comprehensive biographical information linking all the criteria\n- Inability to access detailed obituary or biographical databases that might contain the family name information (Frank, Steve)\n\nTo complete this research successfully, additional search capabilities would be needed, particularly:\n- Access to comprehensive obituary databases\n- Marine species etymology databases\n- Museum founding records with founder biographical information\n- Magazine publisher historical records\n\n## References\n\n- [Biographical Etymology of Marine Organism Names](https://www.bemon.loven.gu.se/petymol.m.html)\n\n- [List of species named after the COVID-19 pandemic - Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_species_named_after_the_COVID-19_pandemic)\n\n- [2025 Annual Marine Photographer Competition Results](https://m.toutiao.com/a1850620858833992/)\n\n- [Five New Seahorse Species Discovered in Red Sea and Indonesian Waters](https://baijiahao.baidu.com/s?id=1826086105331525678)\n\n- [Automating Venture Capital: Founder assessment using LLM-powered segmentation](https://arxiv.org/abs/2407.04123)\n\n- [Design of an Optimal Testbed for Tracking of Tagged Marine Megafauna](https://arxiv.org/abs/2204.04086)\n</finding>\n\n# Current Step\n\n## Title\n\nResearch Museum Founded 1972-1975 and Magazine Publisher Details\n\n## Description\n\nFind museums established between 1972-1975 that are located on the second floor of a building (as of 2023), and identify their founders who were also long-time magazine editors/publishers. Search for magazine publishers who worked for over 30 years and received awards in 2014.\n\n## Locale\n\nen-US\n\nIMPORTANT: Your response MUST be written entirely in the language specified in the 'Locale' section above (which is en-US). This applies to all sections of your response, including headers, content, and conclusions.\n\nIMPORTANT: Review the 'Completed Research Steps' above carefully. If the information required for the 'Current Step' has already been gathered in previous steps, DO NOT perform new searches. Instead, synthesize the existing information to answer the current step immediately. Only use tools if you are missing specific critical details.", additional_kwargs={}, response_metadata={}, id='596a4779-9f22-4322-ae9e-890998cb389a'), HumanMessage(content='IMPORTANT: DO NOT include inline citations in the text. Instead, track all sources and include a References section at the end using link reference format. Include an empty line between each citation for better readability. Use this format for each reference:\n- [Source Title](URL)\n\n- [Another Source](URL)', additional_kwargs={}, response_metadata={}, name='system', id='3ff0e655-0137-41e1-9226-7f919d13fe23'), AIMessage(content='', additional_kwargs={'refusal': None}, response_metadata={'token_usage': {'completion_tokens': 513, 'prompt_tokens': 12892, 'total_tokens': 13405, 'completion_tokens_details': {'accepted_prediction_tokens': None, 'audio_tokens': None, 'reasoning_tokens': 472, 'rejected_prediction_tokens': None, 'text_tokens': 513}, 'prompt_tokens_details': {'audio_tokens': None, 'cached_tokens': None, 'text_tokens': 12892}}, 'model_provider': 'openai', 'model_name': 'qwen3.5-plus', 'system_fingerprint': None, 'id': 'chatcmpl-c15a42cd-b8c1-9369-80aa-5cd024b71e7d', 'finish_reason': 'tool_calls', 'logprobs': None}, name='researcher', id='lc_run--019c9dd6-4547-7741-a0a6-306022b419f9-0', tool_calls=[{'name': 'wikipedia', 'args': {'__arg1': 'notable deaths January 8 2022'}, 'id': 'call_4b49981e69e64d82acd5c4ee', 'type': 'tool_call'}], invalid_tool_calls=[], usage_metadata={'input_tokens': 12892, 'output_tokens': 513, 'total_tokens': 13405, 'input_token_details': {}, 'output_token_details': {'reasoning': 472}}), ToolMessage(content='Page: Suspicious Russia-related deaths since 2022\nSummary: Since the beginning of 2022, numerous Russia-related people, particularly businessmen and officials, have died under what some sources suggest were suspicious circumstances. Incidents include individuals who have suspiciously fallen out of windows, killed themselves, and died unexpectedly in accidents. \n\n\n\nPage: Deaths in 2026\nSummary: The following notable deaths occurred in 2026. Names are reported under the date of death, in alphabetical order. A typical entry reports information in the following sequence:\n\nName, age, country of citizenship at birth, subsequent nationality (if applicable), what subject was noted for, cause of death (if known), and a reference.\n\nPage: Deaths in January 2022\nSummary: ', name='wikipedia', id='ff68ab78-ee02-41fe-a6a7-fe446b8861d0', tool_call_id='call_4b49981e69e64d82acd5c4ee'), AIMessage(content='', additional_kwargs={'refusal': None}, response_metadata={'token_usage': {'completion_tokens': 114, 'prompt_tokens': 13111, 'total_tokens': 13225, 'completion_tokens_details': {'accepted_prediction_tokens': None, 'audio_tokens': None, 'reasoning_tokens': 67, 'rejected_prediction_tokens': None, 'text_tokens': 114}, 'prompt_tokens_details': {'audio_tokens': None, 'cached_tokens': None, 'text_tokens': 13111}}, 'model_provider': 'openai', 'model_name': 'qwen3.5-plus', 'system_fingerprint': None, 'id': 'chatcmpl-b7a2f2a2-0bdf-967a-8ff2-c77c42eea290', 'finish_reason': 'tool_calls', 'logprobs': None}, name='researcher', id='lc_run--019c9dd6-8e71-7561-a9e2-def8a2f730a1-0', tool_calls=[{'name': 'common_search', 'args': {'query': '"January 8, 2022" death obituary magazine publisher founder'}, 'id': 'call_4e49ac32f9524e488635d8e1', 'type': 'tool_call'}], invalid_tool_calls=[], usage_metadata={'input_tokens': 13111, 'output_tokens': 114, 'total_tokens': 13225, 'input_token_details': {}, 'output_token_details': {'reasoning': 67}}), ToolMessage(content=[{'type': 'text', 'text': '# 搜索结果\n标题：The Billionaires Who Died In 2022 - Forbes\nURL：https://www.forbes.com/sites/conormurray/2022/12/31/the-billionaires-who-died-in-2022/\n站点名称：\n发布时间：\n摘要：\nWorld’s Billionaires, published in April 2022.\nAmong the deceased are Edward "Ned" Johnson III, who led giant mutual fund firm Fidelity as CEO for nearly 40 years, Red Bull energy drink cofounder Dietrich Mateschitz and Julian Robertson, a hedge fund pioneer who founded Tiger Management in 1980. 2007.\nAFP via Getty ImagesPierre Bellon\nCitizenship: France\nNet worth at death: $4.2 billion\nDied: January 2022 at age 92\nBellon founded catering company Sodexo in 1966, serving as chairman for 50 years until his daughter, Sophie, took over in 2016. Sodexo expanded internationally in 1971 and as of 2021 served 100 million people in 64 countries daily. Bellon is the author of two books: I\'ve Had A Lot Of Fun: The Sodexo Story, published in 2006, and', 'id': 'lc_b86b860a-af92-41c2-820d-1b785a993db5'}], name='common_search', id='8c56f097-cb6c-43d2-ac5b-a2ede1999395', tool_call_id='call_4e49ac32f9524e488635d8e1'), AIMessage(content='', additional_kwargs={'refusal': None}, response_metadata={'token_usage': {'completion_tokens': 93, 'prompt_tokens': 13461, 'total_tokens': 13554, 'completion_tokens_details': {'accepted_prediction_tokens': None, 'audio_tokens': None, 'reasoning_tokens': 47, 'rejected_prediction_tokens': None, 'text_tokens': 93}, 'prompt_tokens_details': {'audio_tokens': None, 'cached_tokens': None, 'text_tokens': 13461}}, 'model_provider': 'openai', 'model_name': 'qwen3.5-plus', 'system_fingerprint': None, 'id': 'chatcmpl-ae4db84b-14b6-91ac-acaa-e81ff2a62934', 'finish_reason': 'tool_calls', 'logprobs': None}, name='researcher', id='lc_run--019c9dd6-a21c-7b61-8ff0-33531d44714d-0', tool_calls=[{'name': 'common_search', 'args': {'query': '"three species" named after "magazine" publisher died 2022'}, 'id': 'call_92a240286ecf41d296287067', 'type': 'tool_call'}], invalid_tool_calls=[], usage_metadata={'input_tokens': 13461, 'output_tokens': 93, 'total_tokens': 13554, 'input_token_details': {}, 'output_token_details': {'reasoning': 47}}), ToolMessage(content=[{'type': 'text', 'text': '# 搜索结果\n', 'id': 'lc_054ba61b-2387-4054-b9fc-b50192ed1433'}], name='common_search', id='fef8ac2d-36ab-4ad7-ac5f-a8985e7fe41d', tool_call_id='call_92a240286e